text: The Lewis Bridge over the Keya Paha River is a historic bridge listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1992. The bridge carries a county road over the Keya Paha River, 13.6 miles northeast of Springview, Nebraska, spanning between Keya Paha County, Nebraska and Tripp County, South Dakota. and ==References== == External links == *More photos of the Lewis Bridge (Keya Paha River) at Wikimedia Commons Category:Bridges completed in 1922 Category:Buildings and structures in Keya Paha County, Nebraska Category:Buildings and structures in Tripp County, South Dakota Category:Road bridges on the National Register of Historic Places in Nebraska Category:Road bridges on the National Register of Historic Places in South Dakota Category:Road bridges in Nebraska Category:Road bridges in South Dakota Category:National Register of Historic Places in Tripp County, South Dakota Category:Pratt truss bridges in the United States Category:Metal bridges in the United States Category:1922 establishments in Nebraska Category:1922 establishments in South Dakota Category:Pony truss bridges
